  "prompt": "Why do I see the same questions in my Quora feed even if I refresh?",
  "response": "If you're seeing the same questions in your Quora feed despite refreshing, there could be several reasons for this:\n\n1. **Algorithmic Prioritization**: Quora uses algorithms to prioritize content it believes is most relevant to your interests based on your past activity and preferences. If certain questions match these interests closely, they might keep appearing in your feed.\n\n2. **Limited New Content**: At times, there may be a lack of new, high-quality content related to the topics or questions you're interested in. This can result in older questions being shown repeatedly.\n\n3. **Engagement Metrics**: Questions with high engagement (likes, answers, shares) tend to get more visibility. If a question is particularly popular, it might remain prominent in feeds for longer periods.\n\n4. **Subscription and Follow Settings**: If you're following specific topics, people, or questions, you may repeatedly see new updates or answers related to them in your feed.\n\n5. **Cache Issues**: Sometimes, browser or app cache issues may cause older content to repeatedly load. Clearing your cache or restarting the app might help in such cases.\n\n6. **Custom Feeds**: If you have curated your Quora feed by selecting specific interests, the content may not refresh frequently if those topics don't have new questions or answers regularly.\n\nIf this repetition becomes bothersome, you can try adjusting your feed preferences, following new topics, or providing feedback to Quora regarding the content you're seeing.",
